   1. Add to packages: Add the program to your home.packages list in home.nix.
   2. Add to loop: Add NAME = "NAME"; to the configs block in home.nix.
   3. Create the files: Run your terminal commands:
   
   mkdir -p ~/nixos-config/config/NAME
   touch ~/nixos-config/config/NAME/configfile.type
   
   4. Write your config: Open that file in Neovim and add your desired settings.
   5. Stage and Activate: Open your terminal in ~/nixos-config/ and run:
   
   git add .
   rebuild
   
   
## Why Step 5 is Magic ✨
Because of the way you set this up, you only have to do this full sequence the very first time you install an app.
Once that symlink is created by your rebuild, you can skip steps 1, 2, and 5 entirely for that application. 
If you want to tweak that app's settings next week, next month, or next year, you just open its file in ~/nixos-config/config/NAME/ and change it. The update happens instantly!
